  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">2014-17 Organizing Urban Poor To Deal With Evictions And Gain Land Tenure Security &amp; Basic Services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">New additional focus for 2016:
-Jobs for urban poor
- Establishment of Peoples Planning Bureau
- Organizing of Out-of-city resettlement
- CO Training w/ COM
- United urban poor groups
 

Project activities include:
Community Organizing
- Land tenure and housing in BASECO and Tondo
- Expansion of Manila wide Federartion to influence governance processes

Legal work
- lobbying for UDHA amendments

Media work
- Awareness building campaign 

General Eviction work
- Monitoring and research work to influence policies and practices

Tutoring and Other community work
- Tutoring and networiking</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to contribute to both local and national change in providing access to basic social services, security of land tenure and housing, and capacity building of marginalized urban poor.</narrative>
  </description>
